Since the current subtask is "waiting for the program to start", and according to the screenshot provided, you can see that LibreOffice Impress has been successfully started, and now the template selection interface is displayed. Therefore, no action is required to wait for the program in the next step. Instead, you should continue to select a new presentation template.
However, since the task requirement is only "waiting for the program to start", we can use a WaitAction with a very small waiting time (such as 0.1 seconds) to simulate the completion of the waiting process and be ready for the next step, such as selecting a template.```json
[
    {"action_type": "WaitAction", "wait_time": 0.1}
]
```Completing this action means that the program has started and we are ready for the next step. The next operation can be to select a template, and then click "Open" to continue creating the presentation document.
